modules.description: This module generates cryptographically secure random values, including integers, floating-point numbers, bytes, strings, and sequences. It supports operations for creating random data of specific sizes, such as 8-bit to 64-bit integers, and provides functions for generating random alphanumeric characters or custom data structures like `Cstruct.t` and bigarrays. Concrete use cases include generating secure tokens, random identifiers, cryptographic keys, and test data with controlled entropy.
